# TherapyTime End-User Documentation

TherapyTime is a desktop application used to manage student therapy sessions during an IEP period. It helps you:

- track planned and completed sessions,
- monitor required versus completed minutes,
- manage student review and reevaluation dates,
- view day-by-day and student-by-student statistics.

## 1. Getting Started

When the app opens:

1. You are prompted to create/open an IEP date range from the Welcome screen.
2. The main calendar view loads for that IEP.
3. A reminder popup appears for upcoming Annual Reviews and 3-Year Reevaluations in the next 30 days.

### Data Storage

TherapyTime stores data in two logical places:

- Core student data (name, archive status, monthly required minutes, review dates)
- IEP-specific data (sessions and IEP required/received totals)

This allows student identity and long-term dates to persist across multiple IEP files.

## 2. Main Navigation

The top menu contains:

- File
- Student
- Statistics
- Help

### File Menu

- New/Open IEP: Create a new IEP period or open an existing IEP file.
- Save IEP: Save all current changes.
- Exit: Close the application.

### Student Menu

- Add Session
- New Student
- Update Required Minutes
- Archive Student
- Unarchive Student
- Delete Student

### Statistics Menu

- Student Minutes and Sessions (Current IEP)
- Daily View (Current IEP)
- Review and Reevaluation Dates

### Help Menu

- Documentation: Opens the GitHub README in your browser.
- About: Shows app version information.

## 2.1 In-Window Help Bubbles

Every window now includes a `?` help bubble in the top area.

- Click the `?` button in any window to open contextual guidance.
- Each help bubble explains:
	- the purpose of that window,
	- what key controls are for,
	- how to complete common tasks,
	- what important statuses/colors/rules mean.

Window-by-window help coverage:

- Welcome: creating new IEPs vs opening existing IEPs, date range and overlap behavior.
- Main Calendar: menu usage, day-button meaning, and completion color indicators.
- Add Student: required vs optional fields and how review/reevaluation dates are used.
- Add Session: field meanings, IEP range checks, and overlap checks.
- Edit Day Sessions: grid actions, completion workflow, MU/NM linking, and save options.
- Session Notes: editable vs read-only notes behavior.
- Makeup Session Selector: how to choose an NM session for MU linking.
- Student Minutes and Sessions: metric meanings and status color interpretation.
- Daily View: week navigation and day-cell color meaning.
- Review and Reevaluation Dates: highlighted 30-day compliance dates.
- Day View (legacy): purpose and relationship to the current day-edit workflow.

## 3. Calendar View and Day Buttons

The calendar displays each day in the active IEP range.

- A day without sessions shows only the day number.
- A day with sessions shows day number + session count.
- Border colors summarize completion:
	- Green: all sessions completed
	- Amber: mixed completion
	- Red: no sessions completed

Click any day to open the day editor for session management.

## 4. Student Management

### 4.1 Add a New Student

Open Student -> New Student.

Required fields:

- Student Name
- Required Minutes
- Future Annual Review date
- Next 3-Year Reevaluation date

Optional field:

- Past Annual Review date

After saving, the student is immediately available for scheduling.

### 4.2 Update Required Minutes

Open Student -> Update Required Minutes and choose a student.

This updates the student's required minutes target used in current statistics and balancing.

### 4.3 Archive / Unarchive Student

- Archive removes the student from Add Session lists while keeping historical data.
- Unarchive makes the student active again.

### 4.4 Delete Student

Delete permanently removes the student from the current dataset. If sessions exist in the IEP range, a detailed warning is shown first.

## 5. Session Management

### 5.1 Add Session

Open Student -> Add Session.

You select:

- Student
- Date
- Time
- Minutes
- Session Code

Validation rules include:

- Date must fall within the IEP range.
- Session time cannot overlap an existing session on that same day (global conflict check across all students).

### 5.2 Edit Sessions for a Day

Click a day on the calendar to open the day editor.

Capabilities:

- Add and remove sessions for that date.
- Toggle completion status.
- Save Sessions (save and stay in window).
- Save and Exit.
- Cancel Changes.

### 5.3 Completion and Minute Accounting Rules

Current rule behavior:

- Only `T` and `MU` contribute to received therapy minutes.
- `R`, `A`, `SU`, `IC`, and `NM` do not add to received minutes.
- Required minutes are user-controlled and are not automatically reduced by refusal/absence/unavailable codes.

### 5.4 Session Codes

- `IC`: Incomplete / not completed yet
- `T`: Completed therapy session
- `NM`: Needs makeup
- `MU`: Makeup session
- `R`: Refused
- `A`: Absent
- `SU`: Student unavailable

## 6. Statistics Views

### 6.1 Student Minutes and Sessions (Current IEP)

Per-student expandable cards provide:

- Needed minutes
- Required minutes
- Completed minutes
- Scheduled minutes
- Excused minutes
- Remaining minutes
- Therapy balance

Each student card includes a session table with color-coded row status.

### 6.2 Daily View (Current IEP)

Shows a weekly matrix:

- Rows: students
- Columns: days in the selected week
- Cell content: session code(s) for that student/day

Color behavior:

- Green: all sessions completed for that day
- Red: today/past day has one or more incomplete sessions
- Neutral gray: future day (no completion requirement yet)

Use week navigation arrows to move backward/forward within IEP weeks.

### 6.3 Review and Reevaluation Dates

Lists all students sorted by name with columns for:

- Past Annual Reviews
- Future Annual Reviews
- 3-Year Reevaluation

Highlight behavior:

- Any future annual review or reevaluation within the next 30 days is bold and yellow.

## 7. 30-Day Review Reminder Popup

At app load and when opening a new IEP, TherapyTime checks active students for:

- Future Annual Reviews within 30 days
- 3-Year Reevaluations within 30 days

If matches exist, a reminder popup lists the dates and students.

## 8. Typical Workflow

1. Open or create an IEP range.
2. Add students with required review/reevaluation dates.
3. Add sessions from Student -> Add Session.
4. Click calendar days to update completion status.
5. Save regularly using File -> Save IEP.
6. Review progress under Statistics views.

## 9. Troubleshooting

### No students available

- Add at least one student using Student -> New Student.

### Cannot add session on chosen date

- Confirm the date is inside the active IEP range.
- Check for time overlap with an existing session.

### Session not appearing where expected

- Confirm session date and time.
- Verify student is not archived.
- Use the Day editor for that exact date to confirm saved entries.

### Build warning about file lock while developing

If running from Visual Studio/CLI and building while the app is open, the executable may be locked by the running process. Close the app instance and rebuild.

